==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Shimmer
<hw>Shim"mer</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Shimmered</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Shimmering</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE.
<ets>schimeren</ets>, AS. <ets>scimerian</ets>; akin to
<ets>sc⟦imac⟧mian</ets>, <ets>sc⟦imac⟧man</ets>, to glitter, D.
<ets>schemeren</ets>, G. <ets>schimmern</ets>, Dan. <ets>skimre</ets>,
Sw. <ets>skimra</ets>, AS. <ets>sc⟦imac⟧ma</ets> a light, brightness,
Icel. <ets>sk⟦imac⟧ma</ets>, Goth. <ets>skeima</ets> a torch, a lantern,
and E. <ets>shine</ets>. ⟦root⟧157. See <er>Shine</er>, <pos>v.
i.</pos>]</ety> <def>To shine with a tremulous or intermittent light; to
shine faintly; to gleam; to glisten; to glimmer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>shimmering</qex> glimpses of a stream.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shimmer</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Shimmer
<hw>Shim"mer</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A faint, tremulous light; a
gleaming; a glimmer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>TWo silver lamps, fed with perfumed oil, diffused . . . a
trembling twilight-seeming <qex>shimmer</qex> through the quiet
apartment.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shimmering</ent>⟦br⟧
